Justice and Development Party incorporated them. As Tuğal reveals, the absorption of a radical movement was not simply the foregone conclusion of an inevitable world-historical trend but an outcome of contingent struggles. With a closing comparative look at Egypt and Iran, the book situates the Turkish case in a broad historical context and discusses why Islamic politics have not been similarly integrated into secular capitalism elsewhere.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aCapitalismxReligious aspectsxIslamxTurkey. 0aCapitalismxReligious aspectsxIslam. 0aIslam and politicsxTurkey. 0aIslam and politicszTurkey. 0aIslamic fundamentalismxTurkey. 0aIslamic fundamentalismzTurkey. 0aIslamic modernismxTurkey. 0aIslamic modernismzTurkey. 7aRELIGION / Islam / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080477117740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804771177423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804771177.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles